  number   = {1–3},
  pages    = {115-122},
  abstract = {The theoretical basis and design aspects for a capacitance transducer for structural analysis of two-phase gas/liquid flow are presented. The sensor makes it possible to measure gas and liquid distribution, fractions and velocities under transient conditions. A new principle for electric field focusing is presented. With only a few electrodes, sufficient information can be obtained to create near tomographic pictures of the liquid flow. The electrodes are put non-intrusively on a suitable pipewall and the sensor will in its final version be completely computerized.},
